item.description:
Enable SSH Add an file to the boot partition called &ldquo;ssh&rdquo;. This enables you to connect to the pi via ssh.
Enable WiFi To enable wifi on the raspberry pi add a file named &ldquo;wpa_supplicant.conf&rdquo; to the boot partition. Add following content to this file and adapt it to your needs.
ctrl_interface=DIR=/var/run/wpa_supplicant GROUP=netdev country=&lt;Insert 2 letter ISO 3166-1 country code here&gt; update_config=1 network={ ssid=&#34;&lt;Name of your wireless LAN&gt;&#34; psk=&#34;&lt;Password for your wireless LAN&gt;&#34; }
